WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:900000,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:00:12.345 --> 00:00:15.932 position:50% align:center
[TSUKI] Darjeeling? Or maybe
chamomile would be better?

00:00:16.016 --> 00:00:18.184 position:50% align:center
Oh, I just don't know!

00:00:18.268 --> 00:00:19.936 position:50% align:center
I really should have
asked Hana which tea

00:00:20.020 --> 00:00:22.814 position:50% align:center
would be best before
she left earlier.

00:00:22.897 --> 00:00:26.317 position:50% align:center
[MAN A] You're all I have.
Don't you understand?

00:00:26.401 --> 00:00:29.529 position:50% align:center
Please. Can you imagine
if you were being serious?

00:00:29.612 --> 00:00:31.156 position:50% align:center
I'm far too old for you.

00:00:31.239 --> 00:00:33.616 position:50% align:center
[MAN A]
I am serious! I swear!

00:00:33.700 --> 00:00:34.617 position:50% align:center
[WOMAN A gasps]

00:00:34.701 --> 00:00:37.370 position:50% align:center
Wow. That's a big
age difference!

00:00:37.454 --> 00:00:41.583 position:50% align:center
--[clock chimes]
--[TSUKI gasps] Oh, my!

00:00:41.666 --> 00:00:43.960 position:50% align:center
Hana's friend should
be here soon.

00:00:44.044 --> 00:00:45.962 position:50% align:center
I do hope they're nice.

00:02:17.762 --> 00:02:20.098 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
Listen, Mr. Upstanding Guy.

00:02:20.181 --> 00:02:23.768 position:50% align:center
I get that you wanna return what
I paid ya for the mess I made,

00:02:23.852 --> 00:02:26.563 position:50% align:center
but my mom's already
said you don't have to.

00:02:26.646 --> 00:02:29.274 position:50% align:center
Stop. You gave me too much.

00:02:29.357 --> 00:02:33.653 position:50% align:center
If you won't take it, then I'll
just have to return it directly.

00:02:33.737 --> 00:02:36.990 position:50% align:center
It's only too much because you
bought such a cheap replacement.

00:02:37.073 --> 00:02:40.201 position:50% align:center
This was your chance
to get a good one!

00:02:40.285 --> 00:02:44.164 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI grunts]
You sure are quiet today.

00:02:44.247 --> 00:02:45.415 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI gasps]

00:02:45.498 --> 00:02:48.126 position:50% align:center
Hold on a second,
are you actually nervous?

00:02:48.209 --> 00:02:50.628 position:50% align:center
Don't tell me, is this your
first time ever visiting

00:02:50.712 --> 00:02:52.005 position:50% align:center
a girl's house?

00:02:52.088 --> 00:02:54.466 position:50% align:center
That's correct. And I think
I might just throw-up.

00:02:54.549 --> 00:02:57.719 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI] Boy, you surrender
fast when you're cornered.

00:02:57.802 --> 00:03:00.138 position:50% align:center
What do you think my
home's like, anyway?

00:03:00.221 --> 00:03:02.932 position:50% align:center
You act like you're walking
into a haunted house!

00:03:03.016 --> 00:03:05.185 position:50% align:center
Don't worry. You won't get
gobbled up or anything.

00:03:05.268 --> 00:03:06.728 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI grunts]

00:03:06.811 --> 00:03:08.855 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI] And we have
all-you-can-pet cats!

00:03:08.938 --> 00:03:10.940 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:03:11.024 --> 00:03:13.651 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
Wow, talk about a one-eighty.

00:03:13.735 --> 00:03:16.905 position:50% align:center
Are you only doing this
because there will be cats?

00:03:16.988 --> 00:03:19.115 position:50% align:center
Yeah, why? Is it that obvious?

00:03:19.199 --> 00:03:21.326 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI grunts]

00:03:21.409 --> 00:03:23.912 position:50% align:center
Well, now I'm ticked.

00:03:23.995 --> 00:03:25.538 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
Okay, here we are!

00:03:25.622 --> 00:03:28.458 position:50% align:center
Don't worry. I told Mom
I'd be bringing you along.

00:03:30.543 --> 00:03:32.671 position:50% align:center
I'm here!

00:03:32.754 --> 00:03:34.964 position:50% align:center
Hi, honey! Glad you're back!

00:03:35.048 --> 00:03:36.299 position:50% align:center
I'm Hana's mom!

00:03:36.383 --> 00:03:39.636 position:50% align:center
Hana, is this the college
friend you've mentioned?

00:03:39.719 --> 00:03:42.263 position:50% align:center
She's told me an
awful lot about you!

00:03:47.560 --> 00:03:51.690 position:50% align:center
[TSUKI] Scary! He's got
such a penetrating glare!

00:03:51.773 --> 00:03:53.358 position:50% align:center
This is no ordinary fellow.

00:03:53.441 --> 00:03:55.819 position:50% align:center
He's so... intense.

00:03:55.902 --> 00:03:59.197 position:50% align:center
Also, she never told me her
older friend was a boy!

00:03:59.280 --> 00:04:02.784 position:50% align:center
Anyway, you're very
welcome here.

00:04:02.867 --> 00:04:05.286 position:50% align:center
Thank you, ma'am. I'm Sakurai.

00:04:05.370 --> 00:04:06.413 position:50% align:center
I owe you.

00:04:06.496 --> 00:04:08.081 position:50% align:center
You replaced my futon.

00:04:08.164 --> 00:04:09.708 position:50% align:center
I'm so grateful.

00:04:09.791 --> 00:04:13.378 position:50% align:center
[TSUKI] My! He's more
well-mannered than he looks.

00:04:13.461 --> 00:04:14.587 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
However.

00:04:14.671 --> 00:04:16.172 position:50% align:center
I'd like to return some
of what you gave me

00:04:16.256 --> 00:04:18.133 position:50% align:center
since it was more than I needed.

00:04:18.216 --> 00:04:19.759 position:50% align:center
[giggles nervously]

00:04:19.843 --> 00:04:21.469 position:50% align:center
[TSUKI]
Little overwhelmed, here!

00:04:21.553 --> 00:04:23.638 position:50% align:center
His eyes are so fierce!

00:04:23.722 --> 00:04:25.223 position:50% align:center
Hey, mister.

00:04:25.306 --> 00:04:27.851 position:50% align:center
Quit standing around chatting in
the foyer and come in already!

00:04:27.934 --> 00:04:30.353 position:50% align:center
[TSUKI]
What?! He's coming in?

00:04:30.437 --> 00:04:32.772 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI] I'll return the
money and be on my way.

00:04:32.856 --> 00:04:35.942 position:50% align:center
[TSUKI]
Of course. We mustn't keep him!

00:04:36.026 --> 00:04:37.235 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
Mm?

00:04:39.362 --> 00:04:40.739 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI gasps]

00:04:42.282 --> 00:04:45.201 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
Very well. If you insist.

00:04:45.285 --> 00:04:46.703 position:50% align:center
[TSUKI giggles nervously]

00:04:49.456 --> 00:04:54.127 position:50% align:center
[TSUKI] Okay. I think I
understand the situation.

00:04:54.210 --> 00:04:57.339 position:50% align:center
You're saying that Hana offered
too much money for the futon,

00:04:57.422 --> 00:04:59.549 position:50% align:center
so you want to give
back the rest?

00:04:59.632 --> 00:05:01.009 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI, UZAKI]
That's right.

00:05:01.092 --> 00:05:03.595 position:50% align:center
I tried to give it to Hana,
but she wouldn't take it.

00:05:03.678 --> 00:05:05.221 position:50% align:center
I hate to barge in on you,

00:05:05.305 --> 00:05:07.974 position:50% align:center
but returning it directly
was the right thing to do.

00:05:08.058 --> 00:05:10.685 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
He used my name!

00:05:10.769 --> 00:05:13.146 position:50% align:center
Honey? A word?

00:05:13.229 --> 00:05:15.065 position:50% align:center
Huh? What's up?

00:05:16.316 --> 00:05:17.692 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI groans]

00:05:17.776 --> 00:05:19.069 position:50% align:center
[TSUKI] All you've ever told
me is you're spending time

00:05:19.152 --> 00:05:20.653 position:50% align:center
with a "good friend at college"!

00:05:20.737 --> 00:05:22.864 position:50% align:center
Since when do you spend
the night at a boy's place,

00:05:22.947 --> 00:05:24.240 position:50% align:center
you sneaky little thing?

00:05:24.324 --> 00:05:25.575 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
That hurts!

00:05:25.658 --> 00:05:28.244 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
Shoulda seen this coming.

00:05:28.328 --> 00:05:29.913 position:50% align:center
He's one of the
good ones, though!

00:05:29.996 --> 00:05:31.664 position:50% align:center
Really, I swear!

00:05:31.748 --> 00:05:34.167 position:50% align:center
[TSUKI] Young lady, you know
that's not the point!

00:05:34.250 --> 00:05:36.670 position:50% align:center
You might be just fine,
but Sakurai's still...

00:05:36.753 --> 00:05:39.255 position:50% align:center
Well, he's... You know!

00:05:39.339 --> 00:05:40.924 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
Can't even argue.

00:05:42.967 --> 00:05:44.969 position:50% align:center
I think I get what's happening.

00:05:45.053 --> 00:05:47.764 position:50% align:center
This girl of mine has actually
been a terrible bother to you, 

00:05:47.847 --> 00:05:49.015 position:50% align:center
hasn't she?

00:05:49.099 --> 00:05:51.768 position:50% align:center
Oh, no, don't say that.

00:05:51.851 --> 00:05:54.270 position:50% align:center
But, yes. Please, do continue.

00:05:54.354 --> 00:05:55.480 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
Sakurai!

00:05:55.563 --> 00:05:56.940 position:50% align:center
What the heck, dude?

00:05:57.023 --> 00:05:59.359 position:50% align:center
So, my looking after you is
nothing but a big bother?

00:05:59.442 --> 00:06:00.485 position:50% align:center
Really?

00:06:00.568 --> 00:06:02.362 position:50% align:center
No, I wouldn't say
that's exactly true.

00:06:02.445 --> 00:06:04.614 position:50% align:center
About one time out of ten,
I'm grateful for it.

00:06:04.698 --> 00:06:07.701 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
That's a crap average! You suck!

00:06:07.784 --> 00:06:09.786 position:50% align:center
[TSUKI] I think I'm getting
a pretty clear idea 

00:06:09.869 --> 00:06:12.372 position:50% align:center
of how their time
together has been going.

00:06:12.455 --> 00:06:17.002 position:50% align:center
Goodness. They do seem
awfully close, though.

00:06:17.085 --> 00:06:19.587 position:50% align:center
I think Sakurai must
be good for Hana.

00:06:19.671 --> 00:06:22.632 position:50% align:center
Both as an upperclassman
and as a friend.

00:06:22.716 --> 00:06:24.134 position:50% align:center
He may look a
little frightening,

00:06:24.217 --> 00:06:26.302 position:50% align:center
but he seems normal enough.

00:06:26.386 --> 00:06:28.596 position:50% align:center
All that worry for nothing.

00:06:28.680 --> 00:06:32.851 position:50% align:center
Still. My Hana, bringing a
boy home to meet me?

00:06:32.934 --> 00:06:35.020 position:50% align:center
It could be that I'll have some
other things to worry about 

00:06:35.103 --> 00:06:36.771 position:50% align:center
before too long!

00:06:36.855 --> 00:06:38.648 position:50% align:center
Or not!

00:06:38.732 --> 00:06:40.191 position:50% align:center
[TSUKI gasps]

00:06:40.275 --> 00:06:44.154 position:50% align:center
[TSUKI] Am I imagining it or is
Sakurai staring right at me?

00:06:44.237 --> 00:06:45.613 position:50% align:center
Well, not at me...

00:06:45.697 --> 00:06:48.074 position:50% align:center
At my... chest?

00:06:51.494 --> 00:06:54.748 position:50% align:center
[TSUKI] His eyes are fixed on
this one spot. Shameless!

00:06:54.831 --> 00:06:58.543 position:50% align:center
We barely met and he's
already after my body?

00:06:58.626 --> 00:07:01.546 position:50% align:center
He couldn't possibly want
me <i>and</i> my daughter?

00:07:04.257 --> 00:07:07.052 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
Man, I love cats.

00:07:07.135 --> 00:07:09.179 position:50% align:center
You ready to
start petting, or what?

00:07:09.262 --> 00:07:10.597 position:50% align:center
[TSUKI]
Hana!

00:07:10.680 --> 00:07:13.725 position:50% align:center
I mean... if it's okay.

00:07:13.808 --> 00:07:16.019 position:50% align:center
[TSUKI]
What? Sakurai!

00:07:16.102 --> 00:07:17.854 position:50% align:center
You probably can't just yet.

00:07:17.937 --> 00:07:19.522 position:50% align:center
She's on high alert.

00:07:19.606 --> 00:07:21.191 position:50% align:center
She needs to approach you.

00:07:21.274 --> 00:07:22.776 position:50% align:center
[TSUKI]
"Probably"? "Yet"?!

00:07:22.859 --> 00:07:24.861 position:50% align:center
She's kinda shy with strangers.

00:07:24.944 --> 00:07:27.030 position:50% align:center
[TSUKI]
What is she talking about?

00:07:27.113 --> 00:07:29.240 position:50% align:center
If you stop by enough,
she'll get used to you.

00:07:29.324 --> 00:07:30.700 position:50% align:center
Believe me, before you know it,

00:07:30.784 --> 00:07:32.619 position:50% align:center
she's gonna end up
chasing <i>you</i> down!

00:07:32.702 --> 00:07:34.954 position:50% align:center
[TSUKI] Absolutely not!
There is no chance of that!

00:07:35.038 --> 00:07:36.247 position:50% align:center
What are you even saying?

00:07:36.331 --> 00:07:38.667 position:50% align:center
And right in front
of your mother?!

00:07:38.750 --> 00:07:40.043 position:50% align:center
You're right.

00:07:40.126 --> 00:07:42.295 position:50% align:center
Man. Not gonna fly today.

00:07:42.379 --> 00:07:43.588 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:07:45.340 --> 00:07:47.967 position:50% align:center
But soon... I wanna hold her.

00:07:48.051 --> 00:07:50.428 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:07:50.512 --> 00:07:51.846 position:50% align:center
Okay.

00:07:51.930 --> 00:07:54.349 position:50% align:center
Now that we've settled things,
guess I'll get going.

00:07:54.432 --> 00:07:55.225 position:50% align:center
[TSUKI]
Uh.

00:07:55.308 --> 00:07:56.810 position:50% align:center
What? You're leaving so soon?

00:07:56.893 --> 00:07:59.729 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI] Yeah. I don't want
to overstay my welcome.

00:07:59.813 --> 00:08:01.064 position:50% align:center
Well, I um...

00:08:01.147 --> 00:08:02.524 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI] Then why don't
I come to your place?

00:08:02.607 --> 00:08:04.609 position:50% align:center
We can get some gaming in!

00:08:04.693 --> 00:08:07.237 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
Sure, whatever.

00:08:07.320 --> 00:08:09.114 position:50% align:center
Sorry to intrude.

00:08:09.197 --> 00:08:10.365 position:50% align:center
Goodbye.

00:08:10.448 --> 00:08:12.701 position:50% align:center
I'll see you later, Mom, okay?

00:08:14.661 --> 00:08:16.454 position:50% align:center
[TSUKI]
Why is my heart pounding?

00:08:16.538 --> 00:08:18.415 position:50% align:center
The heck is going on with me?

00:08:18.498 --> 00:08:20.041 position:50% align:center
[meows]

00:08:24.295 --> 00:08:27.090 position:50% align:center
Thanks so much! Come again!

00:08:27.173 --> 00:08:29.050 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
Here you go, Mom.

00:08:29.134 --> 00:08:30.468 position:50% align:center
[TSUKI]
Thanks, honey.

00:08:30.552 --> 00:08:33.722 position:50% align:center
I have get back to work,
so you can relax and enjoy that.

00:08:33.805 --> 00:08:36.558 position:50% align:center
Good luck! I'll be here!

00:08:37.726 --> 00:08:41.396 position:50% align:center
[TSUKI] I'm so glad I could see
Hana working at her first job.

00:08:41.479 --> 00:08:44.733 position:50% align:center
And I'm glad I'm getting
to see this side of her.

00:08:44.816 --> 00:08:46.443 position:50% align:center
But...

00:08:48.611 --> 00:08:51.823 position:50% align:center
[TSUKI] ...I never thought
Sakurai would be here, too!

00:08:53.074 --> 00:08:54.409 position:50% align:center
Well, hello!

00:08:54.492 --> 00:08:56.536 position:50% align:center
I heard through the grapevine
that you're Hana's mom?

00:08:56.619 --> 00:08:58.413 position:50% align:center
[ASAI]
So young!

00:08:58.496 --> 00:09:00.040 position:50% align:center
It's very nice to meet you.

00:09:00.123 --> 00:09:02.125 position:50% align:center
You've been so kind
to my daughter.

00:09:02.208 --> 00:09:04.502 position:50% align:center
No, no. She's good to us.

00:09:04.586 --> 00:09:07.422 position:50% align:center
Hana's an extremely
hard worker, you know.

00:09:07.505 --> 00:09:10.508 position:50% align:center
I understand this is her
first part-time job, too.

00:09:10.592 --> 00:09:12.469 position:50% align:center
Guess it's her cheery
disposition that helps her

00:09:12.552 --> 00:09:14.846 position:50% align:center
develop such a rapport
with customers.

00:09:14.929 --> 00:09:16.431 position:50% align:center
Oh, wow, is that right?

00:09:16.514 --> 00:09:18.016 position:50% align:center
I'm so glad to hear it.

00:09:18.099 --> 00:09:19.267 position:50% align:center
Totally!

00:09:19.351 --> 00:09:22.520 position:50% align:center
She's a big hit with all
our regulars, too! See?

00:09:22.604 --> 00:09:23.813 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:09:23.897 --> 00:09:25.565 position:50% align:center
Oh my gosh, are you serious?

00:09:25.648 --> 00:09:27.233 position:50% align:center
[MOTHER B]
As a heart attack!

00:09:27.317 --> 00:09:28.568 position:50% align:center
Hello there!

00:09:28.651 --> 00:09:30.278 position:50% align:center
[LITTLE GIRLS]
Hi, Hana!

00:09:30.362 --> 00:09:33.490 position:50% align:center
The children absolutely
adore her.

00:09:33.573 --> 00:09:35.784 position:50% align:center
And she's always more than
happy to spend time with them

00:09:35.867 --> 00:09:37.243 position:50% align:center
when they're bored.

00:09:37.327 --> 00:09:38.620 position:50% align:center
[CAFÉ OWNER] Only when she's
finished with her work,

00:09:38.703 --> 00:09:39.454 position:50% align:center
of course.

00:09:39.537 --> 00:09:41.664 position:50% align:center
Wow! That's fantastic!

00:09:41.748 --> 00:09:44.584 position:50% align:center
Thank you for this. Truly.

00:09:44.668 --> 00:09:47.087 position:50% align:center
As a mother, I was honestly
worried about her,

00:09:47.170 --> 00:09:49.839 position:50% align:center
but I feel a little better now.

00:09:49.923 --> 00:09:52.175 position:50% align:center
Yep. I'm also a parent.

00:09:52.258 --> 00:09:54.427 position:50% align:center
That kind of concern
never goes away.

00:09:54.511 --> 00:09:55.428 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
Yay!

00:09:55.512 --> 00:09:56.971 position:50% align:center
[ASAI]
When it comes down to it,

00:09:57.055 --> 00:10:00.517 position:50% align:center
turning customers into fans is
the service industry's goal.

00:10:00.600 --> 00:10:03.269 position:50% align:center
[ASAI] After all, a fan
is a frequent visitor!

00:10:03.353 --> 00:10:04.688 position:50% align:center
Hana gives them a
reason to come,

00:10:04.771 --> 00:10:06.898 position:50% align:center
which gives us a big advantage.

00:10:06.981 --> 00:10:09.234 position:50% align:center
It's not something a
first-timer is usually able

00:10:09.317 --> 00:10:10.735 position:50% align:center
to pull off.

00:10:10.819 --> 00:10:12.529 position:50% align:center
You've got yourself a winner.

00:10:12.612 --> 00:10:14.030 position:50% align:center
Oh, my!

00:10:14.114 --> 00:10:16.866 position:50% align:center
This high praise is almost
more than I can bear to hear!

00:10:16.950 --> 00:10:19.494 position:50% align:center
I am thrilled to know
that she's so useful.

00:10:19.577 --> 00:10:21.037 position:50% align:center
Full disclosure?

00:10:21.121 --> 00:10:23.915 position:50% align:center
There is one more notable factor
that tends to bring in moms

00:10:23.998 --> 00:10:25.834 position:50% align:center
like them on the regular.

00:10:25.917 --> 00:10:27.502 position:50% align:center
[TSUKI gasps]

00:10:27.585 --> 00:10:31.047 position:50% align:center
[TSUKI]
Oh! Do... Do you mean Sakurai?

00:10:32.215 --> 00:10:34.217 position:50% align:center
[ASAI]
Ah, you know him already, then?

00:10:34.300 --> 00:10:36.803 position:50% align:center
[TSUKI] Mm.
Yes, just a little, of course.

