00:19:02.642 --> 00:19:04.602 position:50% align:center
As long as you know that.

00:19:06.980 --> 00:19:09.733 position:50% align:center
I spy the unlikely sight of the
fierce and hulking Sakurai,

00:19:09.816 --> 00:19:11.234 position:50% align:center
meekly eating crow!

00:19:11.317 --> 00:19:12.819 position:50% align:center
Dude, are you kidding me?

00:19:12.902 --> 00:19:14.779 position:50% align:center
The housewife market
would eat that up!

00:19:14.863 --> 00:19:18.283 position:50% align:center
Ami! Could you be quiet, please?

00:19:18.366 --> 00:19:20.493 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
I prefer the usual Uzaki.

00:19:20.577 --> 00:19:21.578 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:19:21.661 --> 00:19:23.288 position:50% align:center
[CAFÉ OWNER, ASAI]
Ah! There it is!

00:19:23.371 --> 00:19:25.665 position:50% align:center
We're witnessing
Sakurai's famous...

00:19:29.794 --> 00:19:30.712 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI whimpers]

00:19:30.795 --> 00:19:33.631 position:50% align:center
[ASAI]
Look at her! It's working!

00:19:33.715 --> 00:19:35.467 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
Hm?

00:19:35.550 --> 00:19:39.346 position:50% align:center
Ugh, of course. This is
so like you, Sakurai.

00:19:39.429 --> 00:19:40.805 position:50% align:center
Huh? What is?

00:19:40.889 --> 00:19:42.640 position:50% align:center
I'll tell you what!

00:19:42.724 --> 00:19:45.685 position:50% align:center
The way you always say stuff
without even thinking about it!

00:19:45.769 --> 00:19:46.936 position:50% align:center
What the--?!

00:19:47.020 --> 00:19:48.813 position:50% align:center
Pot, meet Kettle, thank you!

00:19:48.897 --> 00:19:50.857 position:50% align:center
Hey, this is all
your fault, anyway!

00:19:50.940 --> 00:19:52.067 position:50% align:center
You can suck it--

00:19:52.150 --> 00:19:53.777 position:50% align:center
No, it's all because
you got carried away!

00:19:53.860 --> 00:19:55.403 position:50% align:center
I just had the best idea ever!

00:19:55.487 --> 00:19:57.197 position:50% align:center
Can we have them start taking
on different personas

00:19:57.280 --> 00:19:58.281 position:50% align:center
for the customers?

00:19:58.365 --> 00:19:59.741 position:50% align:center
Maybe Mondays,
Wednesdays, and Fridays!

00:19:59.824 --> 00:20:01.284 position:50% align:center
I know the older
ladies in particular

00:20:01.368 --> 00:20:03.370 position:50% align:center
will love meek and mild Sakurai!

00:20:03.453 --> 00:20:06.331 position:50% align:center
If we do that, we could hardly
call ourselves a café anymore.

00:20:06.414 --> 00:20:08.708 position:50% align:center
Could you please stop trying to
put different spins on your

00:20:08.792 --> 00:20:09.834 position:50% align:center
father's business plan?

00:20:09.918 --> 00:20:11.461 position:50% align:center
Know what your problem is?

00:20:11.544 --> 00:20:13.546 position:50% align:center
I sure do, and it's you!

00:20:13.630 --> 00:20:15.465 position:50% align:center
[MOTHER A'S DAUGHTER A]
Hey, no fighting!

00:20:15.548 --> 00:20:17.217 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI, UZAKI]
Huh?

00:20:17.300 --> 00:20:19.219 position:50% align:center
[MOTHER A'S DAUGHTER A grunts]

00:20:19.302 --> 00:20:22.055 position:50% align:center
Oh! Welcome, dear.

00:20:22.138 --> 00:20:24.349 position:50% align:center
[MOTHER A]
Hey, now! I'm sorry about that.

00:20:24.432 --> 00:20:26.768 position:50% align:center
She knows it's rude
to butt into things.

00:20:26.851 --> 00:20:31.231 position:50% align:center
Don't worry! We call this kind
of fight a "lovers' quarrel."

00:20:31.314 --> 00:20:32.941 position:50% align:center
--[UZAKI] No way, dude!
--[SAKURAI] It is not!

00:20:34.025 --> 00:20:36.319 position:50% align:center
Here. You can have this.

00:20:36.403 --> 00:20:37.696 position:50% align:center
Make up, okay?

00:20:37.779 --> 00:20:38.988 position:50% align:center
[chuckles]

00:20:42.367 --> 00:20:45.954 position:50% align:center
New low. We just got
scolded by a little kid.

00:20:46.037 --> 00:20:48.373 position:50% align:center
She got us good.

00:20:48.456 --> 00:20:49.916 position:50% align:center
Hey.

00:20:50.000 --> 00:20:52.127 position:50% align:center
You were saying some pretty
weird stuff back there, though.

00:20:52.210 --> 00:20:53.712 position:50% align:center
Which stuff?

00:20:53.795 --> 00:20:57.382 position:50% align:center
Well, you know, like,
about "the usual Uzaki."

00:20:57.465 --> 00:20:58.508 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:20:58.591 --> 00:20:59.801 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
Hm?

00:21:00.969 --> 00:21:04.097 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI] If I'm not careful,
my expression'll slip!

00:21:04.180 --> 00:21:05.932 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
Hey, look.

00:21:07.267 --> 00:21:09.144 position:50% align:center
Huh? We have that ticket!

00:21:09.227 --> 00:21:10.562 position:50% align:center
Let's do it!

00:21:10.645 --> 00:21:11.855 position:50% align:center
Agreed.

00:21:13.690 --> 00:21:16.067 position:50% align:center
Wait, that means...

00:21:16.151 --> 00:21:19.154 position:50% align:center
Looks like congratulations
are in order!

00:21:19.237 --> 00:21:20.363 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI, UZAKI]
Huh?

00:21:20.447 --> 00:21:21.781 position:50% align:center
[FEMALE STAFFER]
You've won the grand prize:

00:21:21.865 --> 00:21:25.618 position:50% align:center
a two-night, one-day trip
for two to Tottori!

00:21:25.702 --> 00:21:26.411 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
Uh...

00:21:26.494 --> 00:21:28.288 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
Wait, what?

00:21:34.461 --> 00:21:36.004 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
Whoa!

00:21:36.087 --> 00:21:40.216 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI] Wow! They really went
all out in the airport, huh?

00:21:40.300 --> 00:21:42.677 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
Uh, I hate to ask this now.

00:21:42.761 --> 00:21:44.262 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
What's up?

00:21:44.346 --> 00:21:47.265 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI] Are you sure you're
okay with me coming with you?

00:21:47.349 --> 00:21:49.059 position:50% align:center
What are you
talking about, weirdo?

00:21:49.142 --> 00:21:51.561 position:50% align:center
It's your trip, too!
We won this prize together.

00:21:51.644 --> 00:21:54.272 position:50% align:center
[GIRL A] Squee!
The Phantom Thief Kid!

00:21:54.356 --> 00:21:56.691 position:50% align:center
This is my very first
time in Tottori!

00:21:56.775 --> 00:21:58.985 position:50% align:center
Just look at you, your eyes
are totally different.

00:21:59.069 --> 00:22:00.528 position:50% align:center
It's like they're
kinder or something!

00:22:00.612 --> 00:22:01.863 position:50% align:center
Oh, shut up!

00:22:01.946 --> 00:22:04.115 position:50% align:center
Hey, those glasses actually
make you look like--

00:22:04.199 --> 00:22:06.493 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI] Aw c'mon, it should
be obvious here!

00:22:06.576 --> 00:22:09.245 position:50% align:center
Can it! You didn't even let
me finish my sentence!

00:22:09.329 --> 00:22:10.580 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
Ugh...!

00:23:46.384 --> 00:23:47.886 position:50% align:center
[ASAI]
I don't get it. Why Tottori?

00:23:47.969 --> 00:23:49.888 position:50% align:center
[SAKAKI]
Well, Ami, let me explain.